}{}$$\begin{equation*} MI(X,Y) \leq \min\left[MI(X,Z),MI(Z,Y) \right].\end{equation*}$$\end{document}

In other words, the indirect dependence between \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
\usepackage{amsmath}
\usepackage{wasysym} 
\usepackage{amsfonts} 
\usepackage{amssymb} 
\usepackage{amsbsy}
\usepackage{upgreek}
\usepackage{mathrsfs}
\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
